.TH "PROJECTX" "1" "June 2026" "Project X 0.91.10" "User Commands"
.hy
.SH NAME
.PP
projectx - DVB demultiplexing and stream repair utility
.SH SYNOPSIS
.PP
\f[B]projectx\f[R] [\f[I]OPTIONS\f[R]] [\f[I]FILE\f[R]\&...]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.PP
\f[B]Project X\f[R] is a free, Java-based utility designed to
demultiplex, clean up, and repair DVB (Digital Video Broadcasting)
transport streams.
European digital radio and television use the DVB standard to broadcast
data; Project X lets you inspect those transmissions, handle a wide
variety of stream types, and correct errors introduced during reception
or recording.
.PP
It can operate both with a graphical user interface (GUI) and in
headless command-line mode, making it suitable for use in automated
workflows and on servers without a display.
.PP
Supported input formats include MPEG-1/2 Transport Streams (TS), Program
Streams (PS/VOB), PVA streams (AVerMedia, Technisat), and recordings
from various set-top boxes (Dreambox, Topfield).
Output can be demultiplexed elementary streams (video, audio, subtitles)
or re-muxed container files.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\f[B]-gui\f[R]
Start with the graphical user interface, even when input files are
provided on the command line.
.TP
\f[B]-?\f[R]
Print a brief usage summary and exit.
.TP
\f[B]-ini\f[R] \f[I]FILE\f[R]
Use \f[I]FILE\f[R] as the configuration file instead of the default
\f[V]\[ti]/.projectx/projectx.conf\f[R].
.TP
\f[B]-out\f[R] \f[I]DIRECTORY\f[R]
Write output files to \f[I]DIRECTORY\f[R] (must already exist).
.TP
\f[B]-name\f[R] \f[I]BASENAME\f[R]
Use \f[I]BASENAME\f[R] as the base name for output files.
.TP
\f[B]-demux\f[R]
Demultiplex the input stream into separate elementary streams (default
action).
.TP
\f[B]-tovdr\f[R]
Convert the input stream to VDR-compatible format.
.TP
\f[B]-tom2p\f[R]
Convert the input stream to MPEG-2 Program Stream (M2P) format.
.TP
\f[B]-topva\f[R]
Convert the input stream to PVA format.
.TP
\f[B]-tots\f[R]
Convert the input stream to MPEG-2 Transport Stream (TS) format.
.TP
\f[B]-filter\f[R]
Apply PID filtering only, without full demultiplexing.
.TP
\f[B]-id\f[R] \f[I]PIDLIST\f[R]
Restrict processing to the PIDs listed in \f[I]PIDLIST\f[R]
(comma-separated decimal or hexadecimal values prefixed with
\f[V]0x\f[R]).
.TP
\f[B]-cut\f[R] \f[I]FILE\f[R]
Load cut/trim points from \f[I]FILE\f[R].
.TP
\f[B]-chp\f[R] \f[I]FILE\f[R]
Load chapter markers from \f[I]FILE\f[R].
.TP
\f[B]-split\f[R] \f[I]SIZE\f[R]
Split output files at \f[I]SIZE\f[R] megabytes.
.TP
\f[B]-log\f[R]
Write a processing log alongside the output files.
.TP
\f[B]-saveini\f[R]
Save the current settings back to the configuration file on exit.
.TP
\f[B]-webif\f[R]
Start the built-in HTTP interface for remote control.
.TP
\f[B]-set\f[R] \f[I]KEY=VALUE\f[R]
Override a single configuration key at runtime.
This option may be repeated to set multiple keys.
.TP
\f[B]-dvx1\f[R]
Enable DVX mode 1: split project file output.
.TP
\f[B]-dvx2\f[R]
Enable DVX mode 2: split output with RIFF header for AC-3 audio.
.TP
\f[B]-dvx3\f[R]
Enable DVX mode 3: split output with RIFF header for MPEG audio.
.TP
\f[B]-dvx4\f[R]
Enable DVX mode 4: split output with RIFF headers for both AC-3 and MPEG
audio.
.SH FILES
.TP
\f[V]\[ti]/.projectx/projectx.conf\f[R]
Default user configuration file.
Created automatically on first run.
If an \f[V]\[ti]/X.ini\f[R] file is found, it is migrated to this
location.
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
\f[V]JAVA_HOME\f[R]
Path to the Java Runtime Environment used to launch Project X.
.SH SEE ALSO
.PP
\f[B]java\f[R](1)
